@node "Intro"
  Yet another collection of Amiga cheat files?  The problems with the others
are that either they've grown quite large (multiple 100's of K) and have
become rather unweildy if one is looking for the cheat to a particular game,
or they're not as complete as they could be (well neither is this one).  This
collection is broken down into smaller groups so that only a small part of
the file needs to be loaded into memory in order to find a particular cheat.
 
  The original programmers, discoverers, and authors of these cheats are many
and diverse members of the Amiga Community.  In most cases, it's probable
that only they know who they are.  Known sources (although not who's done
what) include: "ANARCHY AMIGA", "AMIGA ACTION", "AMIGA FORMAT",
"AMIGA POWER", "CU AMIGA", "Keith Krellwitz", "GAME BUSTERS", "THE ONE", and
"ULTIMATE CHEAT LIST".  All we game players, who've had trouble in the past
and had to resort to "cheats", are in their debt for their assistance and for
which we thank them.  We are also particularly indebted to those individuals
who took the time to transcribe and accumulate them into the large
collections that can be found in various places on and off line.  I would
like to thank two of the compilers: "PostCard Man" and Keith Krellwitz
(KKRELLWI@NMU.EDU) for their contributions, without which, I could not have
created these Amiga Guide files.
                                     
                                      Raymond H. Earle
